@page "/"

<PageTitle>@Title</PageTitle>

<GdsBreadcrumbs Items="@Breadcrumbs" />

<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Flood Online Reporting Tool (FORT)</h1>

<div>
    <p>Multiple groups are responsible for flood risk so the FORT tool will attempt to forward your report to the correct place.</p>
    <p>You can then manage your flood report via this site and see any responses you recieve.</p>
    
    <GdsWarning Text="It is a legal requirement to report past flooding to potential buyers when selling a property." />
    
    <a role="button" draggable="false" data-prevent-double-click="true" class="govuk-button" data-module="govuk-button govuk-button-start" href="@FloodReportPages.Home.Url">
        Start a new flood report
        <svg class="govuk-button__start-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="17.5" height="19" viewBox="0 0 33 40" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <path fill="currentColor" d="M0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z" />
        </svg>
    </a>
</div>

<div>
    <p>You can also update an existing record if you have provided contact details.</p>
    <div class="govuk-inset-text">
        You will require the reference and access code which should have been sent to you in order to use this service.
    </div>

    <a role="button" draggable="false" data-prevent-double-click="true" class="govuk-button" data-module="govuk-button govuk-button-start" href="@FloodReportPages.Overview.Url">
        Manage an existing report
        <svg class="govuk-button__start-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="17.5" height="19" viewBox="0 0 33 40" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <path fill="currentColor" d="M0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z" />
        </svg>
    </a>
</div>